FEATURE — Visual "facility" dashboard: rooms representing subsystems,
characters representing active agents/workers, click for real status

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
CONTEXT
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Replace/extend the existing basic dashboard frontend with a visual,
game-like layout: a grid of distinct "rooms," each representing one
subsystem of the pipeline, with small animated character icons inside
each room representing active agents/workers. Clicking a room or
character opens a panel showing real, live status pulled from the
actual backend — not decorative or fake activity.

Before writing anything, check what the existing dashboard frontend
is built with (plain HTML/JS, a JS framework, templates served by
FastAPI, etc. — check app/api/routes/dashboard.py and wherever its
frontend assets live) and build on top of that stack rather than
introducing a new framework unless the existing setup genuinely can't
support this.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
ROOM LAYOUT — map each room to a REAL subsystem, not a generic label
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Design roughly one room per major pipeline stage, each wired to its
real corresponding backend piece:

  - Research Room       → AutonomyWorker / TrendResearchAgent
  - Planning Room        → Planner / TaskService (task lifecycle states)
  - Content Room          → Executor, SEO/listing generator agents
  - Image Studio Room     → ProductImageAgent, SocialImageAgent,
                            PODDesignAgent, ImageValidationService
  - QA Room               → QA validation/repair pipeline
  - Storefront Room       → Etsy listing pipeline (EtsyImageService,
                            AUTO_PUBLISH_LISTINGS status)
  - Marketing Room        → MarketingService, PinterestChannel,
                            SEOPostingService
  - Fulfillment Room      → EtsyReceiptWorker, PODFulfillmentService,
                            FulfillmentRecord statuses
  - Ledger Room           → AnalyticsService, RevenueService,
                            PerformanceService, BestProductsService

Adjust naming/grouping if the actual codebase's boundaries don't map
cleanly to this list — check real service/agent boundaries before
finalizing room names, don't force a mismatch.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
DATA — real only, polling existing endpoints
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Do NOT invent new fake activity or placeholder animations disconnected
from real state. Each room's "liveliness" (whether its character is
shown as active/idle/error) must be derived from real data:

  - Worker-backed rooms (Research, Fulfillment): use GET /health/workers
    (already built in step 86) — heartbeat age determines
    active/idle/stale.
  - Task-lifecycle rooms (Planning, Content, QA): query recent Task
    rows by status (use existing TaskService, expose a new lightweight
    read-only endpoint if one doesn't already return this — e.g.
    GET /dashboard/rooms/status summarizing counts per room from real
    queries).
  - Image Studio: recent ImageAsset creation activity (step 76's
    ImageCatalogService).
  - Storefront/Marketing/Ledger: recent PODProduct, MarketingPost,
    AnalyticsEvent activity respectively.

Add ONE new aggregating endpoint (e.g. GET /dashboard/rooms/status)
that returns a per-room summary object rather than making the frontend
call 8 different existing endpoints separately — check current data
in one request, poll it every 5-10 seconds from the frontend.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
INTERACTIVITY
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

- Clicking a ROOM opens a panel showing: current status (active/idle/
  error), a short real summary (e.g. "3 tasks in QA," "last fulfillment
  2 min ago"), and the most recent few real log lines or events
  relevant to that subsystem (reuse existing LogService/AnalyticsService
  queries — don't build a second logging system).
- Clicking a CHARACTER (representing a specific worker/agent) shows
  which real worker/agent it represents and its real current state
  (heartbeat age, last action, error if any).
- No action buttons that DO anything from this view (no triggering
  tasks, no publishing listings) — this is a read-only visualization,
  not a control panel. Keep it that way; don't blur into an admin
  action surface without a separate explicit decision to do so.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
VISUAL STYLE — CSS ONLY, no generated images
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Reference aesthetic: a grid of distinct, colorfully-lit isometric-ish
rooms (like a facility/dungeon map), each with its own accent color
and small character sprites inside.

Build this entirely with CSS Grid/Flexbox for room layout, simple SVG
or small icon-based "character" representations (a colored dot/icon
with a subtle idle animation, e.g. gentle bob/pulse via CSS keyframes)
rather than a full sprite-animation system or any generated artwork.
Give each room its own accent color/glow via CSS box-shadow/border/
gradient, consistent with a dark tech/sci-fi theme. Use CSS transitions
for the click-to-open status panels rather than a heavier animation
library, unless one is already in use elsewhere in the frontend.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
WORKING METHOD
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Check the existing dashboard code/frontend stack first. Build the new
aggregating status endpoint, wire it to real data only, build the
room-grid UI with click-to-inspect panels, and confirm every number/
status shown traces back to a real query — no hardcoded/demo values
left behind. Test by triggering a real task locally (or checking
against current Railway state) and confirming the relevant room
reflects it within one poll interval.

Changelog entry documenting the new endpoint, the room-to-subsystem
mapping chosen, and confirmation that no fake/demo data remains in the
final version.